<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-16393] camel-jsonpath - results from $.concat(...) seems to be cached on following calls</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-16393</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The first result from $.concat(...) seems to be &quot;cached&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Eg, given json:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;{{&lt;/p&gt;
{&quot;payload&quot;: \{&quot;id&quot;: 1, &quot;first_name&quot;: &quot;Marie&quot;, &quot;last_name&quot;: &quot;Rose&quot; }
&lt;p&gt; }}}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The expression:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;jsonpath(&quot;$.concat($.payload.first_name,\&quot; \&quot;,$.payload.last_name)&quot;)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Will always returns &lt;em&gt;Marie Rose&lt;/em&gt; on following calls with different values in the input json.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please find attached reproducer maven project with junit test.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
